Edward S. RICH, Appellant, v. NU-ENAMEL PAINT COMPANY, Inc., a Corporation, et al., Appellees. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. November 23, 1929. No. 5621. J. D. Skeen, of Salt Lake City, Utah, and George Sergeant, of Dallas, Tex., for appellant. John Davis, of Dallas, Tex. (P. D. Crawford and John Davis, both of Dallas, Tex., on the brief), for appellees.

Before WALKER and BRYAN, Circuit Judges, and DAWKINS, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

No ruling complained of being properly presented for review, the judgment is affirmed.
